Sea-life conservation sets for the @getcocofloss holiday collection!

So grateful that for the sixth year (!!), I was asked to illustrate the holiday packaging for Cocofloss. We decided to give some endangered sea-life animals a tropical holiday party.

$10 from each set purchased goes towards an ocean-conservation cause of your choice: the Global Penguin Society, MarAlliance, or polar bear conservation.

Thank you for following my work this year! 2022 felt slow at times (compared to 2021, which was extremely busy life- and art-wise for me), but putting this collection together helped me reflect on how grateful I am. This past week, I had the honor of painting a mural at @acehotelpalmsprings, titled Superbloom. Every April, just before Coachella, a new artist gets the opportunity to  paint a mural here. I was so happy to have been selected for 2023!

I’ll probably have a few posts about this experience as I wait for all the process photos/videos to roll in, but thought I’d start off sharing a little bit about the art. 

In the spring in the Mojave desert, wildflowers erupt and transform the landscape into a rainbow of color and life. Joshua trees, California poppies, creosote bushes, and towering yucca plants are a few of my favorites. I’ve also included some local wildlife- the Mojave Green Rattlesnake, Painted Lady Butterfly, and Costa’s Hummingbird. A band of rainbow holds everything in place, representing the LGBTQIA+ presence in Palm Springs. Finally, stargazing in the Mojave can’t be beat, so I’ve included several stars and celestial elements.

Thanks @acehotelpalmsprings for the amazing staff and all the love we felt over the past week, @tokotah_skye for organizing, and @anitazc for the assistance!

See my new mural at @acehotelpalmsprings come to life! 

For this mural I used a doodle grid (thought up by @r_o_n_e) which is my favorite way to plan out murals on big walls. When I first arrived, I made several doodles all over the white wall, then took a picture of the doodles, then superimposed the wall onto my digital artwork. This way I knew exactly where everything was supposed to go! Much easier to work this way than with a traditional line grid. 

Thanks to @guapsoto, who captured every day so beautifully. And to @anitazc for the assist!

As part of my collaboration with @acehotelpalmsprings, we created a limited edition print based loosely on the mural I painted. 

I incorporated several of the same elements as the mural, but in a different layout and limited color scheme.

This 18x24 3-color silk screen was beautifully printed by @shoestringpressny, and is a signed edition of 100 prints. 

They’re now available for purchase, link to the Ace shop is in my bio! ✨

From Here to Sunday and Natalie Andrewson present Cat Café: a show of feline friend
group exhibition & fundraiser

Opening Reception: Saturday, June 24, 1-6pm

Featuring work by:
•  Ana Krent •  Felize Camille • Jen Tong •  Jia Sung •  Joel Alter •  Karyn Lao •  Kelsey Short •  Kim Sandara •  Kim Sielbeck •  Marisha Lozada •  Maritsa Patrinos •  Miwa Neishi •  Natalie Andrewson •  Nellie Le •  Radhia Rahman •  Rose Wong •  Sarula Bao •  The Lucky Neko •  Thomas Colligan •  Tory Sica • Xiao Mei Chan •

As a continuation of Natalie Andrewson’s Café series at From Here to Sunday, we are presenting a group show based on the multi-faceted world of our furry friends with some of our beloved human friends!

Cats have always played a significant role in the shop’s personality. The lucky cat is one of the first to greet you during a visit, and traditionally, they not only provide a welcoming presence, they act as a symbol of good luck. For Cat Café, we consider all the ways in which cats bring comfort and joy, with a dash of authenticity and sass. Our feline friends represent our ability to be vulnerable through setting boundaries, and the sense of home and fierce loyalty we bring to the ones we love.

Sometimes it feels like the shop itself is going through its own nine lives. From Here to Sunday has evolved and weathered many storms over the years, and looking ahead, it is inevitable that more will come. The one constant that has kept us going is our community, so it only felt appropriate to extend the invitation to our community of artists and host a fundraiser to help sustain this business.

Each artist has generously donated work that will be raffled off to our loving community! Stay tuned for details on how to enter.

I know. I’m all over the place:

2. One of my favorite artists is @davidbyrneofficial. This whole album, Everything That Happens Will Happen Today, is one I revisit all the time. It reminds me of graduating college and NYC. One Fine Day always makes me cry. 
3. @wilco was one of my top bands in high school, I wrote a whole AP Art History essay on them (and passed!). Watching @thebearfx inspired me to revisit their music, and living in a very dark place in California with very bright stars makes this song extra special. 
4. One of my favorites. @carlyraejepsen works extremely hard to put out consistently solid music that is the best to sing along to at the top of your lungs while stuck in traffic (right @chrissyvim?). I love the synth heavy disco-ish songs on this new album!!!

@worldwidewalls , @studiohale , and @alohademele are thrilled to finally share some details on a very special project we’ve been eagerly working on. We have spent the last few weeks gathering works donated by creative friends and colleagues in Hawaii and around the globe to create a unique online gallery, where all proceeds will go towards Maui relief efforts and families who lost their homes in the August 8th wildfire disaster. My new collaboration with @laulimahawaii is out now! 🐌 

A little about this special project from Laulima’s site: 

Kāhuli (Hawaiian land snails) are some of the rarest creatures on Earth. Once common throughout the Hawaiian Islands, less than half of the original 750+ species remain today. This print aims to raise awareness of kāhuli and advocate for their protection. Made in collaboration with artist Kim Sielbeck, this print showcases nine endemic species that each represent their home island(s): Hiona pilsbryi (Kauaʻi), Laminella sanguinea (Oʻahu), Lyropupa striatula (Maui), Succinea konaensis (Hawaiʻi), Newcombia canaliculata (Molokaʻi), Partulina variabilis (Lānaʻi), Carelia sinclairi (Niʻihau), Pleuropoma laciniosa kahoolawensis (Kahoʻolawe), and Endodonta christenseni (Northwestern Hawaiian Islands).

🐌 

I absolutely loved learning about these special little snails (which are drawn way larger than life)! Working with @laulimahawaii has been a dream- I love all their efforts to raise awareness of native Hawaiian flora and fauna through such thoughtful goods.

Shirts, water bottles, totes, and more are now available through the @laulimahawaii shop!

Happy New Year!!!

I guess this really should’ve been drawn over “2023” since this is more of a recap of the past year, but most of it I’m taking with me into the new year, too (Except moving. Moving can stay in 2023 😂). 

We adopted our wild child @livelaughlaika. I found a greater sense of community appreciation, friendship, and family, and got to see so many loved ones this year. We moved to Las Vegas and bought a house.  And I have continued to find so much joy in this art calling. ✨❤️

Cheers to a very happy, healthy, magical, laughter-filled year! Excited for what’s to come.

It’s me, hi, I’m the artist it’s me!

It’s been a while since I’ve shown my face on here, so I took the opportunity to get some headshots by @photos4thepeople (we had the best time!!) and added my own twist.

Some things about me if you’re new around here:

- I LOVE color and pattern. I worked as a textile designer full-time for almost 8 years in NYC before going freelance!
- I am a 100% dog person and love our boxer mix puppy Laika, who you will see in several pieces. My sister’s dog Ziggy was a huge presence in my earlier work and still pops up!
- I’ve moved more times than I can count due to being a military kid, and now a mil spouse. I’m pretty good at being the new kid? I also love meeting new people and seeing new places which helps.
- Creating art brings me so much joy, especially when it’s done with the community or promoting businesses with heart and soul. More of that in 2024!
- Life update!! if you made it to the last slide, you’ve learned that Bryce and I are expecting our first kiddo at the end of April! We’re so excited for the adventure, and can’t wait to meet our little guy. Art moms/dads, tell me your secrets of how you do it all! 

Thanks for tuning in, I’m glad you’re here 🩷 Happy New Year!
